    h1.bd-title#content Scrollspy
    p.bd-lead Automatically update Bootstrap navigation or list group components based on scroll position to indicate which link is currently active in the viewport.
    
    h2#how-it-works How it works
    p Scrollspy has a few requirements to function properly:
    ul
        li
            | If you’re building our JavaScript from source, it 
            a(href='/docs/getting-started/javascript/#util')
                | requires 
                code.highlighter-rouge util.js
            | .
        li
            | It must be used on a Bootstrap 
            a(href='/docs/components/navs/') nav component
            |  or 
            a(href='/docs/components/list-group/') list group
            | .
        li
            | Scrollspy requires 
            code.highlighter-rouge position: relative;
            |  on the element you’re spying on, usually the 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
            | .
        li
            | When spying on elements other than the 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
            | , be sure to have a 
            code.highlighter-rouge height
            |  set and 
            code.highlighter-rouge overflow-y: scroll;
            |  applied.
        li
            | Anchors (
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;a&gt;
            | ) are required and must point to an element with that 
            code.highlighter-rouge id
            | .
    p
        | When successfully implemented, your nav or list group will update accordingly, moving the 
        code.highlighter-rouge .active
        |  class from one item to the next based on their associated targets.
